         I take your point.  Perhaps I am overreacting to the posts on this Board of 58-60th level necros getting owned by caster mobs who, sometimes, are many levels below them.  A perfect example:  The scribe in lower guk.  Already a tough solo even at my level.  I predict it will be impossible now.  </P><P>   I think one of the problems with caster mobs and their increase is the speed at which they cast spells.  As humans, contrary to Alan's short-sighted view, we are not as mechanically efficient as a computer toon.  Thus, just like when you play games like Starcraft or Empire Earth, you have to make up for lack of speed and precision with better strategy.  People are missing this point entirely.  Every single strategy game that comes out has those two truths: Human pcs have better AI and computer toons have better mechanics and game speed.  When it comes to comparing PCs and NPCs AI, Yes...we have it over them, but they have it over us in sheer speed and the ability to perform multiple actions in a shorter space of time.  Timing is everything.  Humans always lose out on that side of the equation.  The more power mobs have, the less effective our strategy advantage becomes.</P><P>53rd Heretic of Misty Knight (Tholluxe Paels)</P><P>Edited by - necrro on 06/07/2002  07:47:17<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
